The purpose of this test strategy is to ensure that the Smart Library Management System (SLMS) meets its functional requirements and operates correctly under different conditions.

Testing mainly focused on verifying:

Book management operations

User actions (Member, Librarian, Administrator)

System constraints (e.g., borrow limit)

Correct implementation of Object-Oriented behaviour

Functional Testing
Ensures that each feature works as expected:

Borrowing books

Returning books

Reserving books

Adding books

Boundary Testing
Tests limits of the system:

Borrowing limit (maximum 5 books)

User Interaction Testing
Tests system behaviour based on user roles:

Member

Librarian

Administrator

Negative Testing
Tests how the system handles invalid inputs:

Wrong login credentials

Borrowing unavailable books

